name: 100% RAW MULTI PURPOSE AFRICAN BLACK SOAP!
description:
Have you heard about African black soap? This all-natural soap was the beauty secret of many Africans for centuries, but it has now become a NATURAL SOAP product worldwide!

Our family loves keeping bulk African Black Soap on hand in our freezer year round! We use it as a multi-purpose soap for our entire household! READ MORE!

Black Soap Benefits

Here are some of the most significant benefits of African black soap:

  • It possesses antibacterial properties – the strong antibacterial properties make it an amazing natural cleanser

  • It has anti-inflammatory properties – the ashes in the black soap contain sulfur which possesses strong anti-inflammatory and antimicrobial properties. While the rough texture of the product exfoliates the skin, this active ingredient eliminates fungus and bacteria on the skin, whether that’s the face or any other part of the body.

  • It moisturizes the skin – it contains oils that help trap the water in the skin, thus preventing excessive water loss from bathing. Along with the soap’s anti-inflammatory properties, the moisturizing ability helps soothe irritation linked to psoriasis and eczema. While the black soap is surprisingly healing for some skin types, for others it may be a tad drying. That’s why it’s important to know how to use African black soap for your skin type.

  • It improves the tone and texture of the skin – the soap’s rough texture allows it to exfoliate the dead, hyper-pigmented skin cells.

  • It reduces dandruff – the ashes in the African black soap contain anti-inflammatory and antifungal properties which help destroy the yeast that causes dandruff. What’s more, the oils in the soap help moisturize the dry scalp.

Don’t use too much African soap, especially if you have dehydrated skin.

Here’s how to use it:

  • Wet your face with warm water.

  • Wet the soap until you notice a lather.

  • Rub the soap gently on your skin – face and body – in a circular motion avoiding the eyelids. Avoid the eyes and intimate parts.

  • Rinse your skin with warm water.

  • Apply a moisturizing cream.

Can You Use African Black Soap for All Skin Types?

Even though you can use black soap for the face, you should be careful and not use it too often. Generally, the product is ideal for combination skin or skin with oily T-zone.

Overuse can significantly dry out your skin.

Don’t use too much African soap, especially if you have dehydrated skin.

How to use African Black Soap as a facial cleanser:

  • Wet your face with warm water.

  • Wet the soap until you notice a lather.

  • Rub the soap gently on your skin – face– in a circular motion avoiding the eyelids. Avoid the eyes.

  • Rinse your skin with warm water.

    Apply a moisturizing cream.

Our African Black Soap is hand-made in West Africa.

This BEAUTIFUL soap is an excellent cleanser that is composed of numerous soothing and beneficial ingredients that are abundantly found in plants!

Although these ingredients are found all through the world, Black Soap is traditionally made by hand in Africa.

Black soaps contain various oils, like the coconut oil, palm oil, palm kernel oil, shea butter and cocoa butter. They also contain ashes from different plants, like shea tree bark, banana trees, cocoa pods, and plantain leaves.

Along with these water is used as a base for producing these BEAUTIFUL & AMAZING SOAPS!

We store our Black Soap in large gallon size freezer bags and keep it in the freezer for long term storage!

We use our Black Soap for every cleaning purpose in our house! I simply take a small bar of soap and place it into a mason jar with water. Allow the soap to naturally dissolve overnight, by the next morning stir the “liquid soap” and add to your empty soap pump container!

I always keep a Hand Pump Soap in each bathroom sink and in the showers and on my kitchen sink as a replacement for Dish Soap! I absolutely LOVE having my own “liquid soap” on demand and in bulk supply in my freezer!

I also love African Black Soap as a body wash, shampoo, and facial cleanser!

It’s truly an amazing healthy product to have in you household!

If you choose to use your African Black Soap in the “BAR FORM”

Here is a recommended way to store it:

Keep your black soap in a cool and dry place, preferably cut into small balls and store in a plastic bag.

This will help avoid the formation of a thin white film that appears when the soap is exposed to the air.

If you leave it exposed, your African soap may soften and gradually disintegrate due to the glycerin content.

Plus, it absorbs water so it’s best to keep it dry. You can drain it on a wooden soap dish before putting it in a plastic bag.

name: Yarba Mate Loose Leaf Tea Traditional South American Health Tea BULK 1 POUND
description:
A TRADITIONAL TEA: Yerba Mate has been used for centuries in South America as a natural stimulant to support mental clarity and focus.

Yarba Mate offers "the strength of coffee, benefits of tea, and the euphoria of chocolate".

Yarba Mate is a powerful and all natural, appetite curbing tea that provides energy, improves digestion and boosts your immune system.

Yarba Mate is often found in “Health Food Green Powder Suppliments”

Yarba Mate Contains:

Xanthines: These compounds are stimulants. They include caffeine and theo bromine, commonly found in tea, coffee, and chocolate.

  • Caffeoyl derivatives: These compounds are the main antioxidants in the tea.

  • Saponins: These bitter compounds have strong anti-inflammatory and cholesterol-lowering properties.

  • Polyphenols: These antioxidants are linked to a reduced risk of many diseases.

Interestingly, the antioxidant power of yerba mate tea is actually higher than Green Tea!

Yarba Mate contains seven out of nine essential amino acids, in addition to nearly every vitamin and mineral your body needs!

Now you can enjoy the simplicity of a loose leaf Yarba Mate at home!

You can make Yarba Mate in the traditional way with a Yerba Mate Cup & Bombilla Mate Straw!

We recommend shopping on amazon search for:

8 Oz Yarba Mate Wooden Finish Double Walled Stainless Steel Cup

How To Brew Loose Yerba Mate

  1. Add 1-2 TBS of yerba mate to a French press,strainer, or loose leaf tea infuser of your choice.

  2. Add 8 oz of 170°F water.

  3. Steep 5 minutes and strain.

  4. Sweeten to taste if desired.

description:

LSU Tiger produces a large crop of large brown figs, with darker brown stripes, with a delicious yellow/gold flesh.

Figs have long been enjoyed as a sweet delicacy. They are high in fiber, calcium, potassium, and iron as well as containing other vitamins and minerals. To enjoy figs throughout the year consider drying, canning, or preserving them. Fig leaves can be dried and used as a tea to help regulate blood sugar and other health benefits.
Fig trees do best where they get at least 8 hours of direct sun per day. They are fairly drought tolerant but extended dry periods can cause leaf and fruit drop as well as early dormancy. A deep organic mulch will help to alleviate extremes in moisture levels, reduce nematode issues, as well as to reduce competition from weeds. Figs are a wonderful addition to your backyard or orchard!

description:
This delicious rich coffee is certified as “Fair Trade Organic”

All of our coffee is roasted in The Great State Of Texas!

Harvested: February - May

Processing: Washed

Roast Level: Med/Light

Taste: Creamy & Sugary, Juicy Fruity Notes, Citrus & Berry

name:
Colombia Supremo -
Dark Roast
description: Colombia Supremo, the king of Colombian coffee’s, is known almost as well for its versatility as it is for its flavors. After developing the perfect medium-roast profile to truly showcase the incredible inherent flavors of the Supremo, we knew that this bean had no boundaries. Through countless trials, and hours of cupping, we were able to pinpoint the precise moment in 2nd crack where the natural full-bodied traits danced with hints of roast and brown sugar. It was as if the stars had aligned, creating a dark roast that preserved the qualities of its origin. Whether you use a pour-over, a French press, or a standard drip method, you can always count on the king. All of our coffee is locally roasted in the great State Of Texas!

name: Mexico Turquesa Chiapas Medium Roast
description:
All of our coffee is roasted in The Great State Of Texas!

This Single Origin True Mexican Coffee offers you a sophisticated and clean cup with bright citrus sweetness, delicate chocolate overtones, and complex nutty notes. An Arabica coffee which is "High Grown" in the rich volcanic soil of the Sierre de Madre Chiapas region known as Turquesa, or Turquoise (for the brilliant blue skies), in southern Mexico. These single origin beans are processed by the wet-processed or “washed” method. This means that the fruit skin and pulp were removed from the beans immediately after harvesting and before drying. Additionally, they are put through another level of quality assurance called the "European Prep" method which makes for a much more uniform coffee with no defects. If you enjoy a brew with cocoa/chocolate overtones, this is a great single origin.

name: Justice Espresso
description:
This is our heavy weight espresso for those desiring a rich, darker roast, with lots of velvety & delicious cream. This roast level has been brought to full Vienna roast, a darker roast, but not the heavy oily sheen of other espressos where they roast the flavor out of their beans and only leave the burnt carbon husks. If you want a great tasting espresso that displays the delicate interplay between flavor and the depth of roast, this is it. The trick is to find the sweet spot between the best expression of flavor from the single origins, and contrast that against the right amount of desirable bittersweet & carbony flavors imparted by the roast level. We feel strongly that we have managed to find that sweet spot between these three specialty grade, single origin coffees whereas we have not burnt up all of the delicious sugars, but brought them to a bittersweet stage that display the right amount of deep dark caramel and chocolate undertones with a great amount of body that gives you plenty of volume. This is an impressive espresso displaying a bittersweet edge and perfect for heavy sugar and milk drinks.

All of our coffee is locally roasted in the great State Of Texas!

name: Phoenix Tears Goji Berry
description:
1 Bundle of 5 Cuttings

The Phoenix Tears Goji Berry is a highly nutritious, packed plant. Complete with protein and antioxidants, as well as having higher carotene levels than a carrot.

Light purple, bell-shaped flowers bloom in May and continue throughout the summer months. Phoenix Tears Goji berries have a sweet flavor with a mild acidity. The fruit is often dried, canned, or used in smoothies.

At maturity it reaches 5 to 6 feet tall and 5 feet wide.

Goji Berry plants make a beautiful addition to any backyard homestead, orchard, or edible landscape!

The Phoenix Tears Goji is a self-fertile plant!

Cold and drought tolerant

Neutral or somewhat alkaline soil

Zones:3-8

We recommend spacing these plants 5 - 6' apart to ensure room for growth.
